.TH THEMECTL 1 "2024" "themectl" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
themectl \- unified theming solution for Frog-OS applications
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B themectl
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fICOMMAND\fR [\fIARGS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBthemectl\fR is a unified theming solution that reads TOML theme definitions
and generates configuration files for multiple applications including Kitty,
Waybar, Hyprland, Neovim, Starship, Mako, and more.
.PP
Themes are defined in TOML format and can be applied to all supported
applications with a single command. \fBthemectl\fR automatically detects
configuration file locations and creates backups before making changes.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-themes-dir \fIPATH\fR
Override the default themes directory (default: ./themes)
.TP
.BR \-\-dry-run
Preview changes without applying them
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.BR apply \fITHEME\fR
Apply a theme to all detected applications
.TP
.BR list
List all available themes
.TP
.BR create \fINAME\fR
Create a new theme interactively
.TP
.BR validate \fIPATH\fR
Validate a theme file
.TP
.BR export \fITHEME\fR \fIFORMAT\fR
Export theme to a specific format
.TP
.BR show \fITHEME\fR
Show theme details
.TP
.BR edit \fITHEME\fR
Edit an existing theme interactively
.TP
.BR preview \fITHEME\fR
Preview theme with color swatches and generated configs
.TP
.BR delete \fITHEME\fR
Delete a theme
.TP
.BR rename \fIOLD\fR \fINEW\fR
Rename a theme
.TP
.BR duplicate \fITHEME\fR \fINEW\fR
Duplicate a theme
.TP
.BR search \fIQUERY\fR
Search themes by name or description
.TP
.BR init
Initialize theme directory structure
.TP
.BR variant
Manage theme variants (see \fBthemectl-variant\fR(1))
.TP
.BR config
Manage themectl configuration (see \fBthemectl-config\fR(1))
.TP
.BR backups
Manage backup files (see \fBthemectl-backups\fR(1))
.SH EXAMPLES
Apply a theme:
.RS
.PP
themectl apply gruvbox-dark
.RE
.PP
List available themes:
.RS
.PP
themectl list
.RE
.PP
Export theme to Kitty format:
.RS
.PP
themectl export gruvbox-dark kitty --output kitty.conf
.RE
.PP
Preview a theme:
.RS
.PP
themectl preview gruvbox-dark
.RE
.SH FILES
.TP
.B ~/.config/themectl/config.toml
Configuration file for themectl
.TP
.B ./themes/
Default themes directory
